    "So, Bernstein assumption is satisfied with constant K = 1.",
    "Actually, this can be extended beyond the 0 -1 loss: for any loss ℓ with values in [0, C], if R(θ *) = 0, then Bernstein assumption is satisfied with constant K = C. Example 4.3 (Mammen and Tsybakov margin assumption).",
    "More generally, still in classification with the 0 -1 loss, consider the function Mammen and Tsybakov (1999) proved that, if |η(X i) -1/2| ≥ τ almost surely for some τ > 0, then Bernstein assumption holds for some K that depends on τ.",
